OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A thief has been found guilty of       
OL,6, murdering a pensioner who died after   
OL,7, being tied up in a burglary.           
OL,9,FDavid Varlow, 78, was bound to a chair 
OL,10,Fat his home in Halesowen in November.  
OL,11,FHe suffered a "stress-induced" heart   
OL,12,Fattack, Birmingham Crown Court heard.  
OL,14,FA trial was told Adris Mohammed, 44,   
OL,15,Fforced Mr Varlow to reveal his bank    
OL,16,Fcard PIN.                              
OL,18,FAs well as murder, Mohammed was        
OL,19,Fconvicted of two counts of burglary,   
OL,20,Fattempted burglary and fraud.          
